# Accessibility Guidelines

## WCAG Compliance Standards

### Level AA Compliance Target
- **Perceivable**: Content must be perceivable to all users
- **Operable**: Interface must be operable by all users
- **Understandable**: Content must be understandable
- **Robust**: Content must be robust and compatible

## Semantic HTML Structure

### Document Structure
```html
<!-- Use proper heading hierarchy -->
<h1>Main page title</h1>
<h2>Section heading</h2>
<h3>Subsection heading</h3>

<!-- Use semantic elements -->
<header>, <nav>, <main>, <section>, <article>, <aside>, <footer>
```

### Navigation Accessibility
```html
<!-- Primary navigation -->
<nav role="navigation" aria-label="Main navigation">
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
    <li><a href="/bio">About</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>

<!-- Skip links for keyboard users -->
<a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>
```

## Color and Contrast

### Color Contrast Requirements
- **Normal text**: Minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio
- **Large text**: Minimum 3:1 contrast ratio
- **UI components**: Minimum 3:1 contrast ratio
- **Focus indicators**: High contrast visible

### Color Independence
- **Don't rely on color alone**: Use icons, patterns, or text
- **Test in grayscale**: Ensure information is still conveyed
- **Provide alternatives**: Text descriptions for color-coded information

## Typography and Text

### Font Accessibility
- **Readable fonts**: Sans-serif fonts preferred
- **Adequate size**: Minimum 16px for body text
- **Line spacing**: 1.5x line height minimum
- **Character spacing**: Sufficient letter spacing

### Text Alternatives
```html
<!-- Alt text for images -->
<img src="profile.jpg" alt="Jennifer Andréoli-Fang professional headshot">

<!-- Descriptive link text -->
<a href="/publications">View my research publications</a>

<!-- Skip decorative images -->
<img src="decoration.jpg" alt="" role="presentation">
```

## Keyboard Navigation

### Focus Management
```css
/* Visible focus indicators */
:focus {
  outline: 2px solid #007bff;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* Skip link styling */
.skip-link {
  position: absolute;
  top: -40px;
  left: 6px;
  z-index: 1000;
}

.skip-link:focus {
  top: 6px;
}
```

### Tab Order
- **Logical tab order**: Follow document structure
- **Skip links**: Provide shortcuts to main content
- **Focus traps**: Avoid trapping users in components
- **Keyboard shortcuts**: Provide alternative navigation

## Screen Reader Support

### ARIA Labels and Roles
```html
<!-- Landmark roles -->
<header role="banner">
<nav role="navigation">
<main role="main">
<footer role="contentinfo">

<!-- Descriptive labels -->
<button aria-label="Close navigation menu">×</button>
<section aria-labelledby="publications-heading">
  <h2 id="publications-heading">Publications</h2>
</section>
```

### Content Structure
- **Headings**: Use proper heading hierarchy (H1 → H6)
- **Lists**: Use semantic list elements (`<ul>`, `<ol>`, `<dl>`)
- **Tables**: Include headers and captions
- **Forms**: Include labels and fieldset groups

## Images and Media

### Image Accessibility
```html
<!-- Informative images -->
<img src="research-diagram.jpg" 
     alt="Flowchart showing machine learning pipeline with data preprocessing, model training, and evaluation stages">

<!-- Decorative images -->
<img src="background-pattern.jpg" alt="" role="presentation">

<!-- Complex images -->
<img src="complex-chart.jpg" alt="Bar chart showing quarterly sales data">
<figcaption>Figure 1: Quarterly sales performance 2023</figcaption>
```

### Media Accessibility
- **Video content**: Provide captions and transcripts
- **Audio content**: Provide transcripts
- **Interactive media**: Ensure keyboard accessibility
- **Auto-playing content**: Provide pause/stop controls

## Forms and Interactive Elements

### Form Accessibility
```html
<!-- Proper form structure -->
<form>
  <fieldset>
    <legend>Contact Information</legend>
    <label for="name">Name:</label>
    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>
    
    <label for="email">Email:</label>
    <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
  </fieldset>
</form>
```

### Interactive Elements
- **Buttons**: Use semantic button elements
- **Links**: Provide descriptive text
- **Custom controls**: Include ARIA attributes
- **Error handling**: Provide clear error messages

## Responsive Design Accessibility

### Mobile Accessibility
- **Touch targets**: Minimum 44px × 44px
- **Spacing**: Adequate spacing between interactive elements
- **Zoom support**: Allow zoom up to 200%
- **Orientation**: Support both portrait and landscape

### Responsive Navigation
```css
/* Mobile menu accessibility */
.mobile-menu {
  position: fixed;
  top: 0;
  left: -100%;
  transition: left 0.3s ease;
}

.mobile-menu.active {
  left: 0;
}

/* Focus management for mobile menu */
.mobile-menu:focus-within {
  left: 0;
}
```

## Testing and Validation

### Manual Testing
- **Keyboard navigation**: Test with Tab, Shift+Tab, Enter, Space
- **Screen reader testing**: Test with NVDA, JAWS, or VoiceOver
- **Color contrast**: Use tools like WebAIM Contrast Checker
- **Zoom testing**: Test at 200% zoom level

### Automated Testing
- **Lighthouse**: Run accessibility audits
- **axe-core**: Automated accessibility testing
- **HTML validation**: Check for semantic errors
- **CSS validation**: Ensure proper styling

### Testing Checklist
- [ ] All images have appropriate alt text
- [ ] Color contrast meets WCAG AA standards
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works properly
- [ ] Focus indicators are visible
- [ ] Screen reader compatibility verified
- [ ] Mobile accessibility tested
- [ ] Forms are properly labeled
- [ ] Error messages are clear and helpful

## Performance and Accessibility

### Loading Performance
- **Progressive enhancement**: Core functionality works without JavaScript
- **Graceful degradation**: Site works with limited capabilities
- **Loading indicators**: Provide feedback during loading
- **Error handling**: Clear error messages and recovery options

### Content Accessibility
- **Plain language**: Use clear, simple language
- **Reading level**: Aim for 8th grade reading level
- **Abbreviations**: Define abbreviations on first use
- **Technical terms**: Provide explanations for complex concepts
